Array Basics

-Array variables can store several pieces of data in one place
-Can store any data type in array
var dogs = ['Caroga', 'Titan', 'Chief'];

-Multidimensional array
var colors = [['yellow', 'marigold', 'gold'], ['blue', 'navy', 'cyan'], ['red', 'burgundy', 'ruby']];

-Access elements with index beginning at zero
console.log(dogs[1])
return => Titan

console.log(colors[0][2]);
return => gold
0: first collection of array
2: is the '2nd' element from first collection

console.log(colors[1][0]);
return => blue

-All arrays have forEach method
dogs.forEach(function(element) {
  console.log(element);
})
element is each item in array
return => Caroga
          Titan
          Chief
